<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Testament" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Testament,</orth> a will, a writing by which a person disposes of his property after his death: <bibl n="shak. luc 1183" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1183</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.1.78" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 1, 78</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.1.47" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 5.3.197" default="NO" valid="yes">All's V, 3, 197</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.1.10" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 1, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.6.27" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 6, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.5.17" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 5, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 5.1.30" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 1, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.2.135" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 2, 135</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.2.135" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 2, 135</bibl> <bibl n="shak. per 4.2.107" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 2, 107</bibl>. <cit><quote>he is come to open the purple t. of bleeding war,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.3.94" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 3, 94</bibl></cit>, i. e. he is come to try, who will become heir of England by the decision of war.
